Simon Gear will deliver his last weather report on Radio 702 and Cape Talk on Saturday, after 17 years with the Primedia-owned stations. Gear was on a freelance contract, which was not renewed due to cost-related issues. On Monday, the weatherman shared the news of his departure with his Twitter followers. He later clarified his first tweet. Radio 702 station manager Thabisile Mbete  confirmed the news. “We will say goodbye to him on air this Friday morning and we have wished him well for the future.” Gear has become a household name for his reports and anecdotes. On social media, hundreds of people commented on his departure.